<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord Lyons</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-03-30"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 30, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I duly received your note of the 23d
                            instant, on the subject of an alleged disregard by the United States
                            attorney at Key West of the wishes of this government with reference to
                            the mails of friendly powers found on board of captured vessels.</p>
                        <p>In reply, I have the honor to acquaint you that proper instructions upon
                            the subject have been given to that officer.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be your very obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>